SIMPLE: roughcast
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Roughcast
<hw>Rough`cast"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
form in its first rudiments, without revision, correction, or
polish.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To mold without nicety or elegance; to form with
asperities and inequalities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To plaster with a mixture of lime and shells or
pebbles; <as>as, to <ex>roughcast</ex> a building</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roughcast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Roughcast
<hw>Rough"cast`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A rude model; the
rudimentary, unfinished form of a thing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of plastering made of lime, with a mixture of
shells or pebbles, used for covering buildings.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Roughcaster</ent>⟦br⟧
